The '''Dar Fur Daju''' are an ethnic group in the [[Sudan]]. They are one of seven distinct ethnicities comprising the [[Daju people]]. They speak the [[Nyala language (Sudan)|Nyala language]].<ref name=Ethnologue>[http://www.ethnologue.com/language/daj Ethnologue: "Daju, Dar Fur - A language of Sudan"] retrieved September 1, 2013</ref> They live in [[Southern Darfur]] in the [[Sudan]] in the Daju Hills 40&nbsp;km northeast of [[Nyala]] - although most of this population has fled to Chad as a result of the [[Darfur Conflict]].<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2006/11/19/opinion/19kristof.html New York Times: "The Face of Genocide" By NICHOLAS D. KRISTOF] November 19, 2006</ref> There is also a small population of Dar Fur Daju near the city of Lagowa in the [[Nuba Hills]]. Their total population numbers 80,000 (1993).<ref name=Ethnologue /> They are mostly Muslim.<ref>[http://www.joshuaproject.net/people-profile.php?peo3=11475&rog3=SU Joshua Project: "Daju, Dar Fur of Sudan"] retrieved September 1, 2013</ref>
