The '''Koteka''' of [[West Papua (region)|West Papua]] are seven major ethnicities of the highlands of [[West Papua (region)|West Papua]] with a common culture: the [[Lani people|Lani]], [[Ekari people|Mee]], [[Amung people|Amungme]], [[Moni people|Moni]], [[Damal people|Damal]], [[Yali people|Yali]], and [[Nduga people|Nduga]]. The Koteka share their identity with other peoples in southern [[West Papua (region)|West Papua]], the [[Muyu people|Muyu]], [[Mandobo people|Mandobo]], and [[Kamoro people|Kamoro]].

